  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This raises an interesting possibility: the overall impact of LLMs on collaborative software development, such as in open-source projects, could be stronger than initial experimental results suggest.",
    "The question that arises is whether, in light of the rising popularity of LLMs, workers using LLMs to generate solutions may be disproportionately drawn to tasks with readily verifiable answers and detailed backgrounds.",
    "In voluntary collaborative settings where contributors choose their focus, this self-selection may be particularly pronounced, creating an imbalance between innovation types that might not be as evident in organizational settings with assigned tasks.",
    "Such a tendency may lead to a downward trajectory in architectural solutions, as the ease and efficiency of addressing well-defined problems could overshadow the pursuit of groundbreaking discoveries.",
    "This pattern aligns with Benner and Tushman's (2003) findings that technological and process innovations inadvertently favor exploitative activities over exploratory ones."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "This pattern aligns with Benner and Tushman's (2003) findings that technological and process innovations inadvertently favor exploitative activities over exploratory ones."
  ]
}